<w:document xmlns:wpc="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2010/wordprocessingCanvas" xmlns:cx="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/drawing/2014/chartex" xmlns:cx1="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/drawing/2015/9/8/chartex" xmlns:cx2="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/drawing/2015/10/21/chartex" xmlns:cx3="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/drawing/2016/5/9/chartex" xmlns:cx4="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/drawing/2016/5/10/chartex" xmlns:cx5="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/drawing/2016/5/11/chartex" xmlns:cx6="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/drawing/2016/5/12/chartex" xmlns:cx7="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/drawing/2016/5/13/chartex" xmlns:cx8="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/drawing/2016/5/14/chartex" xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006" xmlns:aink="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/drawing/2016/ink" xmlns:am3d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/drawing/2017/model3d" xmlns:o="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" xmlns:oel="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/2019/extlst" xmlns:r="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/officeDocument/2006/relationships" xmlns:m="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/officeDocument/2006/math" xmlns:v="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:vml" xmlns:wp14="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2010/wordprocessingDrawing" xmlns:wp="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/wordprocessingDrawing" xmlns:w10="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word" xmlns:w="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/wordprocessingml/2006/main" xmlns:w14="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2010/wordml" xmlns:w15="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2012/wordml" xmlns:w16cex="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2018/wordml/cex" xmlns:w16cid="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2016/wordml/cid" xmlns:w16="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2018/wordml" xmlns:w16du="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2023/wordml/word16du" xmlns:w16sdtdh="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2020/wordml/sdtdatahash" xmlns:w16sdtfl="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2024/wordml/sdtformatlock" xmlns:w16se="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2015/wordml/symex" xmlns:wpg="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2010/wordprocessingGroup" xmlns:wpi="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2010/wordprocessingInk" xmlns:wne="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2006/wordml" xmlns:wps="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2010/wordprocessingShape" mc:Ignorable="w14 w15 w16se w16cid w16 w16cex w16sdtdh w16sdtfl w16du wp14"><w:body><w:p w14:paraId="47539C91" w14:textId="2E9271E9" w:rsidR="003434DA" w:rsidRDefault="003434DA" w:rsidP="003434DA"><w:pPr><w:jc w:val="center"/><w:rPr><w:b/><w:bCs/><w:sz w:val="36"/><w:szCs w:val="36"/><w:lang w:val="en-PH"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="003434DA"><w:rPr><w:b/><w:bCs/><w:sz w:val="36"/><w:szCs w:val="36"/><w:lang w:val="en-PH"/></w:rPr><w:t>CHAPTER 1</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="084F00A0" w14:textId="67F15689" w:rsidR="003434DA" w:rsidRDefault="003434DA" w:rsidP="003434DA"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:b/><w:bCs/><w:sz w:val="28"/><w:szCs w:val="28"/><w:lang w:val="en-PH"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:b/><w:bCs/><w:sz w:val="28"/><w:szCs w:val="28"/><w:lang w:val="en-PH"/></w:rPr><w:t>INTRODUCTION</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="6421C216" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="003434DA" w:rsidRPr="003434DA" w:rsidRDefault="003434DA" w:rsidP="003434DA"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="003434DA"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:t xml:space="preserve">The evolution of sales tracking and inventory management systems stems from the growing need to efficiently monitor business operations, particularly in retail and technology-based enterprises. Traditionally, businesses relied on manual methods such as handwritten records and spreadsheets, which often led to inefficiencies and inaccuracies. With the advancement of digital technology, many businesses adopted computerized systems to automate sales tracking and inventory control, improving speed, accuracy, and overall operational efficiency. </w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="7E1FA778" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="003434DA" w:rsidRPr="003434DA" w:rsidRDefault="003434DA" w:rsidP="003434DA"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="003434DA"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:t>In computer retail businesses such as PC Alley, managing sales and inventory effectively is essential to ensure smooth operations and customer satisfaction. These systems are responsible for recording transactions, tracking stock levels, and generating reports that support business decision-making. An integrated system helps maintain consistency between sales and inventory data, ensuring that product availability and pricing are accurately monitored.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="1F68B2DD" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="003434DA" w:rsidRPr="003434DA" w:rsidRDefault="003434DA" w:rsidP="003434DA"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="003434DA"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:t>Despite having an existing system in place, PC Alley currently experiences significant issues related to data accuracy, particularly with historical sales records. One major problem arises when the current price of a product is updated in the system. Instead of preserving the original transaction details, the system also modifies past sales records to reflect the new price. This results in inaccurate sales reports, as historical data no longer represents the actual price at which products were sold. Consequently, this affects financial analysis, profit calculation, and overall business reliability.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="0EA27CF7" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="003434DA" w:rsidRPr="003434DA" w:rsidRDefault="003434DA" w:rsidP="003434DA"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="003434DA"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:t>Accurate historical data is crucial for evaluating business performance, forecasting trends, and making informed decisions. When past transaction records are altered, it compromises the integrity of the system and leads to misleading information. This issue highlights a critical limitation of the current system, particularly in its inability to preserve transaction history independently from product updates.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="0AA0B772" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="003434DA" w:rsidRPr="003434DA" w:rsidRDefault="003434DA" w:rsidP="003434DA"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="003434DA"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:t>To address this problem, the proposed Integrated Sales Tracking and Inventory Management System for PC Alley aims to enhance data integrity by ensuring that all sales transactions retain their original values, regardless of future price changes. The system will be designed to separate transactional data from product data, allowing each sale to store its own fixed price at the time of purchase. This approach ensures that historical records remain accurate and reliable.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="52AA4E3B" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="003434DA" w:rsidRPr="003434DA" w:rsidRDefault="003434DA" w:rsidP="003434DA"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="003434DA"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:t>Additionally, the system will provide features such as real-time inventory tracking, automated stock updates, sales reporting, and low-stock alerts. These functionalities will improve operational efficiency while maintaining accurate and consistent records. By implementing this improved system, PC Alley can achieve better control over its sales and inventory processes, reduce errors, and enhance decision-making capabilities.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="6A8801A7" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="003434DA" w:rsidRPr="003434DA" w:rsidRDefault="003434DA" w:rsidP="003434DA"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="003434DA"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:t>Ultimately, this study focuses on designing and developing a more reliable and efficient system that addresses the limitations of the current setup. By resolving issues related to historical data inaccuracies, the proposed system aims to provide a more dependable solution for managing sales and inventory, contributing to the overall growth and sustainability of the business.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="5F3D22FA" w14:textId="5AFC8CA6" w:rsidR="003434DA" w:rsidRDefault="003434DA" w:rsidP="003434DA"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:b/><w:bCs/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/><w:lang w:val="en-PH"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:b/><w:bCs/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/><w:lang w:val="en-PH"/></w:rPr><w:lastRenderedPageBreak/><w:t>PROJECT CONTEXT</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="080F3D11" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="003434DA" w:rsidRPr="003434DA" w:rsidRDefault="003434DA" w:rsidP="003434DA"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="003434DA"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:t>PC Alley, a computer retail business, plays a vital role in providing computer parts, accessories, and related products to its customers. As the business continues to operate and handle increasing numbers of transactions, it relies on a computerized system to manage sales and inventory. While the presence of an existing system helps streamline operations, certain challenges still persist, particularly in maintaining accurate and reliable data.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="4BA669DA" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="003434DA" w:rsidRPr="003434DA" w:rsidRDefault="003434DA" w:rsidP="003434DA"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="003434DA"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:t>One of the major issues encountered by PC Alley is related to the handling of historical sales data. The current system allows the modification of product prices; however, when a product’s price is updated, the changes are also reflected in past transactions. This results in inaccurate sales records, as previous transactions no longer reflect the actual price at which items were sold. Consequently, this affects the reliability of sales reports, profit calculations, and overall business analysis.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="4A379E45" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="003434DA" w:rsidRPr="003434DA" w:rsidRDefault="003434DA" w:rsidP="003434DA"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="003434DA"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:t>In addition to this, the lack of proper data separation between product information and transaction records leads to inconsistencies in reporting and decision-making. Accurate historical data is essential for evaluating business performance, identifying sales trends, and making strategic decisions. Without a system that preserves the integrity of past records, the business faces difficulties in tracking its true financial standing.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="52BFA13F" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="003434DA" w:rsidRPr="003434DA" w:rsidRDefault="003434DA" w:rsidP="003434DA"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="003434DA"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:t>To address these concerns, the developers propose the creation of an Integrated Sales Tracking and Inventory Management System for PC Alley. This system aims to provide a more reliable and efficient way of managing sales transactions and inventory data. It will include features such as real-time sales tracking, automated inventory updates, and accurate report generation. Most importantly, the system will ensure that each transaction retains its original details, including the product price at the time of sale, regardless of future changes.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="1C99C21C" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="003434DA" w:rsidRPr="003434DA" w:rsidRDefault="003434DA" w:rsidP="003434DA"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="003434DA"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:t>The proposed system will also enhance overall operational efficiency by centralizing data, reducing manual errors, and improving accessibility of information. By implementing this solution, PC Alley will be able to maintain accurate records, improve decision-making, and provide better service to its customers.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="51B865F1" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="003434DA" w:rsidRDefault="003434DA" w:rsidP="003434DA"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="003434DA"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:t>Ultimately, this project seeks to resolve the limitations of the current system by introducing a more advanced and reliable platform. Through this improved system, PC Alley can achieve better organization, data accuracy, and long-term sustainability in its business operations.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="6B641DFD" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00820505" w:rsidRDefault="00820505" w:rsidP="003434DA"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr></w:pPr></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="69A34D74" w14:textId="2D41E340" w:rsidR="00820505" w:rsidRDefault="00820505" w:rsidP="003434DA"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:b/><w:bCs/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:b/><w:bCs/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:t>PURPOSE AND DESCRIPTION</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="5A8C6808" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00820505" w:rsidRPr="00820505" w:rsidRDefault="00820505" w:rsidP="00820505"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="00820505"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:t xml:space="preserve">The study aims to develop an </w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="00820505"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:b/><w:bCs/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:t>Integrated Sales Tracking and Inventory Management System for PC Alley</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="00820505"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:t xml:space="preserve"> that addresses existing issues in data accuracy, particularly in preserving historical sales records. The system is designed to improve business operations by ensuring that past transactions remain unchanged even when product prices are updated. This will lead to more reliable reports, better inventory control, and improved decision-making.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="577FE0F5" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00820505" w:rsidRPr="00820505" w:rsidRDefault="00820505" w:rsidP="00820505"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="00820505"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:t>The study will be advantageous to the following:</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="5FE5FFFA" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00820505" w:rsidRPr="00820505" w:rsidRDefault="00820505" w:rsidP="00820505"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="00820505"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:b/><w:bCs/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:lastRenderedPageBreak/><w:t>PC Alley Business Owner/Management.</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="00820505"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:t xml:space="preserve"> This study will provide the management with a more reliable system that ensures accurate sales and inventory records. It will help them make informed business decisions, monitor profits correctly, and improve overall operational efficiency.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="159A0605" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00820505" w:rsidRPr="00820505" w:rsidRDefault="00820505" w:rsidP="00820505"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="00820505"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:b/><w:bCs/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:t>Store Employees.</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="00820505"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:t xml:space="preserve"> Employees will benefit from a user-friendly system that simplifies sales recording and inventory tracking. It will reduce manual errors, save time, and make daily operations more efficient and organized.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="50E5AC61" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00820505" w:rsidRPr="00820505" w:rsidRDefault="00820505" w:rsidP="00820505"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="00820505"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:b/><w:bCs/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:t>Customers.</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="00820505"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Arial" w:hAnsi="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="22"/><w:szCs w:val="22"/></w:rPr><w:t xml:space="preserve"> Customers will indirectly benefit from improved service, as the system ensures accurate pricing, better stock availability, and faster transaction processing, leading to a smoother purchasing experienc